4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING EDUCATION LAWS TO STRENGTHEN
5 THE STATE'S COMMITMENT TO PRESERVING AMERICAN INDIAN CULTURAL INTEGRITY UNDER
6 ARTICLE X, SECTION 1(2), OF THE MONTANA CONSTITUTION; REVISING INDIAN EDUCATION FOR ALL
7 LAWS TO EMPHASIZE TRIBAL CONSULTATION AND THE ROLE OF INDIAN LANGUAGE AND CULTURAL
8 SPECIALISTS; PLACING ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS ON THE BOARD OF PUBLIC EDUCATION AND
9 THE OFFICE OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION TO IMPROVE INDIAN EDUCATION FOR ALL AND STRENGTHEN
10 ACCOUNTABILITY; CLARIFYING THE DUTIES OF THE OFFICE OF PUBLIC INSTRUCTION FOR
11 FINANCIAL ACCOUNTABILITY OF INDIAN EDUCATION FOR ALL FUNDS PROVIDED BY THE STATE TO
12 SCHOOL DISTRICTS; ESTABLISHING REPORTING REQUIREMENTS; REVISING A DEFINITION;
13 AMENDING SECTIONS 20-1-501, 20-1-502, 20-1-503, 20-7-101, AND 20-9-329, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
14 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
15
16 WHEREAS, Article X, section 1(2), of the Montana Constitution states: "The state recognizes the
17 distinct and unique cultural heritage of the American Indians and is committed in its educational goals to the
18 preservation of their cultural integrity"; and
19 WHEREAS, the Montana Legislature has honored this commitment in several ways, including through
20 the creation of Indian Education for All; and
21 WHEREAS, accountability for school districts in providing Indian Education for All and for the funding
22 provided by the Legislature for Indian Education for All has been lacking; and
23 WHEREAS, this lack of accountability has resulted in costly and protracted litigation.
24
25 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
26
27 Section 1. Section 20-1-501, MCA, is amended to read:
28 "20-1-501. Recognition of American Indian cultural heritage -- legislative intent. (1) It is the
