17 Section 2. Section 20-1-502, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "20-1-502. American Indian studies -- definitions. As used in this part, the following definitions
19 apply:
20 (1) "American Indian studies" means instruction pertaining to the history, traditions, customs,
21 values, beliefs, ethics, language, and contemporary affairs of American Indians, particularly Indian tribal groups
22 in Montana.
23 (2) "Educational agency" means:
24 (a) the Montana university system;
25 (b) professional educator preparation programs accredited by the board of public education;
26 (c) the board of public education;
27 (d) the office of public instruction; and
28 (e) school districts.
