12 Section 5. Section 20-9-329, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "20-9-329. Indian education for all payment. (1) Except as provided in subsection (5), the state
14 shall provide an Indian education for all payment to public school districts, as defined in 20-6-101 and 20-6-701,
15 to implement the provisions of Article X, section 1(2), of the Montana constitution and Title 20, chapter 1, part 5.
16 (2) The Indian education for all payment is calculated as provided in 20-9-306 and is a component
17 of the BASE budget of the district.
18 (3) The district shall deposit the payment in the general fund of the district.
19 (4) (a) A public school district that receives an Indian education for all payment may not divert the
20 funds to any purpose other than curriculum development of an American Indian studies program, providing
21 curriculum and materials to students for the program, and providing training to teachers about the program's
22 curriculum and materials.
23 (b) A public school district shall file an annual report with the office of public instruction, in a form
24 and by a date prescribed by the superintendent of public instruction, that specifies how the Indian education for
25 all funds were expended in the prior school fiscal year in sufficient detail to ensure that all the funds were
26 properly spent for the purposes under subsection (4)(a) In addition to the expenditure reporting, the report must
27 include detailed descriptions of:
28 (i) the instruction provided to certified personnel and students as required under 20-1-503; and
